✨We were delighted to welcome Alma Laura’s son, Luis (@attawalpa) to our Salon Privé of his mothers’s paintings! .
.
🇵🇪 Peruvian artist Alma Laura has developed her painting practice over 50 years whilst living between the UK and South America. In her moving and colour-filled works, she explores her own identity alongside themes of sexuality, race, the feminine, the body, family, the imagined and the current. All from her own internal gaze and memories. Amalgama is proud to be exhibiting her works for the first time.
.
🖼️ If you’d like to have exclusive access to her work today Friday 13 January or Tomorrow, Saturday 14, between 11am and 7pm, please email jane@artamalgama.com.
.
Kindly supported by @theearthvision_org .
